Class BackwardsPath

A path that walks backwards through the graph, i.e. it walks along the directed edges in the reverse direction. The path is described by the nodes in the path. Class is immutable.

The path can have an open or closed edge at the end. An open edge points to the final node in the path, but does not actually include it.
